\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 1. \b0 People spend less time hunting for a tab that they want to switch between. [quantitative]\
\b 2. \b0 Users can better manage the sites that they want to read later but don't want to bookmark. [qualitative] \
\b 3. \b0 People can still move quickly between a small set of tabs (i.e., the random access that the traditional tabs interface gives). [both]\
\b 4. \b0 People keep more tabs open at once while not increasing tab-switch times. [quantitative]\
\b 5. \b0 People garbage collect more aggressively. [quantitative]\
\b 6. \b0 Continues to work well for small sets of tabs. [qualitative]}
